description:
On this second 2023 retrospective episode of ANN International,

ADRA, the Adventist humanitarian agency, has been actively delivering relief amid the Russia-Ukraine conflict.

'I Will Go to My Neighbour' initiative in the Solomon Islands led to a significant surge in baptisms.

Also, thrilling moments at the 13th International Pathfinder Camporee in Sopron, Hungary! Over 2,600 participants from around the world showcased the global impact of the Pathfinder movement.

Stay tuned as ANN brings you these captivating stories and provides coverage of other global news. For a deeper dive into these headlines and more, visit adventist.news.

ANN is the official news channel of the Seventh-day Adventist Church.
